# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Lena Travels — Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# IMPORTANT: This file is a TEMPLATE only. Do NOT add real values here.
# This file is safe to commit. The actual .env.local file is gitignored.
#
# HOW TO CONFIGURE:
#   Local development:
#     1. Copy this file: cp .env.local.example .env.local
#     2. Fill in your real values in .env.local
#     3. .env.local is gitignored — it will never be committed
#
#   Vercel production:
#     1. Go to: Vercel Dashboard → Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#     2. Add each variable below with your real values
#     3. Set scope to: Production, Preview, Development (as needed)
#     4. Redeploy after adding variables
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# EmailJS — Contact Form
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get these from: https://dashboard.emailjs.com/admin
#
# Service ID:   EmailJS → Email Services → your service → Service ID
# Template ID:  EmailJS → Email Templates → your template → Template ID
# Public Key:   EmailJS → Account → API Keys → Public Key

VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=service_im8nd3h
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=template_hc5u01l
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=EhG43MfbwQ-UJex7K

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOTE: All VITE_ prefixed variables are embedded at BUILD TIME by Vite.
# They are NOT secret server-side variables — they are bundled into the
# client-side JavaScript that browsers download. Do not store truly secret
# values (database passwords, private API keys) as VITE_ variables.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
